de.unifrankfurt.informatik.acoli.starling.model

Class TurkicRDFModelBuilder

  • java.lang.Object
    • de.unifrankfurt.informatik.acoli.starling.model.StarlingRDFModelBuilder
      • de.unifrankfurt.informatik.acoli.starling.model.TurkicRDFModelBuilder
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    StarlingRDFModelBuilderI

    public class TurkicRDFModelBuilder
extends StarlingRDFModelBuilder
    This class implements the RDF conversion of the Turkic Starling dictionary.

    Turkic Starling dictionary

    by using a Jena model. It may be also well suited for converting other dictionaries of the Starling Altaic etymology for Mongolian, Tungus, Korean and Japanese.

    Author:
    frank

      • buildWORDS

        public java.lang.Integer buildWORDS(java.lang.Integer recordNr,
                                    java.lang.String elementName,
                                    java.lang.String elementValue)
        Description copied from interface: StarlingRDFModelBuilderI
        Action for any XML element with a name different from PROTO, MEANING, RUSMEAN or NUMBER. Target elements that should be processed are all elements that have a Starling language identifier (3 or 4 letter language code) as their name (e.g. TAT). These actually refer to cognates of the proto-form in the XML PROTO element. Build lemon lexical entries, etc.
        Specified by:
